            <div class="clearfix text-formatted field field--name-field-dl-body field--type-text-with-summary field--label-hidden field__item"><p>Welcome to the Choice Robotics Lab website! The lab is located in the&nbsp;<a href="https://ece.umn.edu/">Department of Electrical and Computer Engineering</a>&nbsp;at the&nbsp;<a href="https://twin-cities.umn.edu/">University of Minnesota (UofM), Twin Cities</a>. The lab name CHOICE stands for&nbsp;<em>Cleverly Helping rObots In Challenging Environments</em>&nbsp;(CHOICE). It also informally means Choi's lab following the PI's last name.&nbsp;</p><p>The long-term research goal of our lab is to design computational learning models that enable robots to&nbsp;</p><ol><li><strong>perceive</strong>&nbsp;the world,</li><li><strong>understand</strong>&nbsp;tasks, and</li><li><strong>perform</strong>&nbsp;manipulation skills&nbsp;</li></ol><p>so that society benefits from affordable, reliable labor forces. Toward this long-term goal, we study&nbsp;<strong>object grasping</strong>,&nbsp;<strong>manipulation</strong>,&nbsp;<strong>object perception</strong>,&nbsp;<strong>reinforcement learning</strong>, and their novel&nbsp;<strong>combinations</strong>&nbsp;(see&nbsp;<a href="./research">Research</a>&nbsp;for details).&nbsp;</p><h4>News</h4><ul><li><strong>Sep 2025</strong>: An ECE Ph.D. student, <a href="https://hantao-ye.github.io/" data-entity-type="external">Hantao Ye</a>, joins the lab.</li><li><strong>Jul 2025</strong>: One paper (<a href="https://sites.google.com/umn.edu/ogrg/" data-entity-type="external">attribute–based object grounding and grasping</a>) is accepted for IEEE-RAS <a href="https://2025humanoids.org/" data-entity-type="external">Humanoids 2025</a>.</li><li><strong>May 2025</strong>: PI promoted to Associate Professor with indefinite <strong>tenure</strong> at UMN.</li><li><strong>Jan 2025</strong>: Two papers (<a href="https://sites.google.com/umn.edu/etog-etrg/" data-entity-type="external">PET for object grasping</a>, <a href="https://ieeexplore.ieee.org/abstract/document/11127451/" data-entity-type="external">DLO routing</a>) are accepted for IEEE <a href="https://2025.ieee-icra.org/" data-entity-type="external">ICRA 2025</a>.</li><li><strong>Jan 2025</strong>: Our paper, <a href="https://www.alireza.page/invslotgnn" data-entity-type="external">InvSlotGNN</a>, an expanded version of our previous ICRA paper (<a href="https://www.alireza.page/slot-gnn">SlotGNN</a>), has been accepted for publication in IEEE&nbsp;<a href="https://www.ieee-ras.org/publications/t-ro">Transactions on Robotics (T-RO)</a>.<br>&nbsp;</li><li><strong>Sep 2024</strong>: An ECE Ph.D. student, <a href="https://hongyoungjin.github.io/" data-entity-type="external">Youngjin Hong</a>, joins the lab.</li><li><strong>Aug 2024</strong>: PI receives a research grant from <a href="https://www.nrf.re.kr/eng/main">NRF</a> in Korea ($450K).</li><li><strong>Aug 2024</strong>: Alireza successfully defended his Ph.D. thesis and will join <a href="https://www.accenture.com/">Accenture</a> as an AI research scientist.</li><li><strong>Jul 2024</strong>: Chase successfully defended his MS thesis and will join <a href="https://www.hp.com/">Hewlett Packard</a> as an engineer.</li><li><strong>Mar 2024</strong>: PI receives the <a href="https://www.sony.com/en/SonyInfo/research-award-program/">Sony Research Award</a> (Faculty Innovation Award, $100K).</li><li><strong>Jan 2024</strong>: Two papers (<a href="https://www.alireza.page/slot-gnn">SlotGNN</a>, <a href="https://lmeee.github.io/DLOInsert/" data-entity-type="external">DLO insertion</a>) are accepted for IEEE <a href="https://2024.ieee-icra.org/">ICRA 2024</a>.<br>&nbsp;</li><li><strong>Dec 2023</strong>: One journal based on our previous ICRA paper (<a href="https://sites.google.com/umn.edu/attributes-grasping">attribute-based grasping</a>) is accepted for IEEE&nbsp;<a href="https://www.ieee-ras.org/publications/t-ro">Transactions on Robotics (T-RO)</a>.</li><li><strong>Aug 2023</strong>: One paper (<a href="https://ieeexplore.ieee.org/document/10214136">KINet</a>) is published in IEEE <a href="https://ieeexplore.ieee.org/xpl/RecentIssue.jsp?punumber=7083369">RA-L</a> and will be presented at IEEE <a href="https://2024.ieee-icra.org/">ICRA 2024</a>.</li><li><strong>Aug 2023</strong>:&nbsp;PI will serve as a Workshop Associate Editor for IEEE <a href="https://2024.ieee-icra.org/">ICRA 2024</a>.</li><li><strong>Jun 2023</strong>: Three papers (IOSG, object rearrangement, mass estimation) are accepted for IEEE/RSJ <a href="https://ieee-iros.org/">IROS 2023</a>.</li><li><strong>May 2023</strong>: PI will give an invited talk at <a href="https://ippc-iros23.github.io/">IROS 2023 IPPC Workshop</a>.</li><li><strong>May 2023</strong>: Xibai successfully defended his Ph.D. thesis and will join <a href="https://www.amazon.science/research-areas/robotics">Amazon Robotics</a>.</li><li><strong>Jan 2023</strong>: One paper (<a href="https://ieeexplore.ieee.org/document/10161191">federated object grasping</a>) is accepted for <a href="https://www.icra2023.org/">ICRA 2023</a>.</li><li><strong>Jan 2023</strong>:&nbsp;PI will serve as an Associate Editor for IEEE/RSJ&nbsp;<a href="https://ieee-iros.org/">IROS 2023</a>.<br>&nbsp;</li><li><strong>Jul 2022</strong>: One paper&nbsp;(<a href="https://sites.google.com/umn.edu/sag-interactive-segmentation">segmentation by manipulation</a>) is accepted for <a href="https://eccv2022.ecva.net/">ECCV 2022</a>.</li><li><strong>Jun 2022</strong>: One paper&nbsp;(<a href="https://ieeexplore.ieee.org/document/9982182">environment-enabled grasping</a>) is accepted for IEEE/RSJ&nbsp;<a href="https://iros2022.org/">IROS 2022</a>.</li><li><strong>May 2022</strong>: One of our ICRA papers (<a href="https://sites.google.com/umn.edu/attr-disam">interactive grasping</a>) won the IEEE&nbsp;<a href="https://www.icra2022.org/">ICRA 2022</a><a href="https://www.icra2022.org/program/awards">&nbsp;Outstanding Student Paper award</a>.</li><li><strong>May 2022</strong>: Yang successfully defended his Ph.D. thesis and joins Meta (a.k.a. Facebook).</li><li><strong>Mar 2022</strong>: PI receives the <a href="https://beta.nsf.gov/funding/opportunities/faculty-early-career-development-program-career">NSF Career Award</a>.</li><li><strong>Feb 2022</strong>: Two papers (<a href="https://sites.google.com/umn.edu/attr-disam">interactive grasping</a>,&nbsp;<a href="https://sites.google.com/umn.edu/graph-grasping">GNN-based grasping</a>) are accepted for IEEE&nbsp;<a href="https://www.icra2022.org/">ICRA 2022</a>.</li><li><strong>Jan 2022</strong>:&nbsp;PI will serve as an Associate Editor for IEEE/RSJ&nbsp;<a href="https://iros2022.org/">IROS 2022</a>.</li><li><strong>Jan 2022</strong>:&nbsp;PI receives the&nbsp;<a href="https://cse.umn.edu/mnri/news/spring-2021-mnri-seed-grant-recipients-announced">MnRI Seed Grant</a>&nbsp;with Prof.&nbsp;<a href="http://jinlab.bbe.umn.edu/">Jin</a>.<br>&nbsp;</li><li><strong>Dec 2021</strong>: PI receives&nbsp;<a href="https://research.umn.edu/funding-awards/ovpr-funding/grant-aid/award-recipients">Grant-in-Aid (GIA)</a>&nbsp;- New Assistant Professor from UMN.</li><li><strong>Dec 2021</strong>: PI receives&nbsp;Russell J. Penrose Excellence in Teaching Award from ECE, UMN.</li><li><strong>Aug 2021</strong>:&nbsp;PI will serve as an Associate Editor for IEEE&nbsp;<a href="http://www.icra2022.org/">ICRA 2022</a>.</li><li><strong>Mar 2021</strong>:&nbsp;PI receives the&nbsp;<a href="https://www.sony.com/electronics/research-award-program">Sony Research Award</a>&nbsp;(Faculty Innovation Award, $100K).</li><li><strong>Mar 2021</strong>: Three papers (<a href="https://sites.google.com/umn.edu/attributes-grasping">attribute-based grasping</a>,&nbsp;<a href="./collision-aware-object-grasping">collision-aware grasping</a>,&nbsp;<a href="https://sites.google.com/umn.edu/ki-dqn/">grasping via fixtures</a>) are accepted for IEEE&nbsp;<a href="http://www.icra2021.org/">ICRA 2021</a>.</li><li><strong>Feb 2021</strong>:&nbsp;PI will serve on Organizing Committee for&nbsp;<a href="http://2021.icrita.org/">RiTA&nbsp;2021</a>&nbsp;as a Special Session Chair and an Associate Editor.</li><li><strong>Feb 2021</strong>: PI will serve as an Associate Editor for IEEE/RSJ&nbsp;<a href="https://www.iros2021.org/">IROS 2021</a>.</li><li><strong>Feb 2021</strong>: A&nbsp;<a href="https://cse.umn.edu/mnri/masters-robotics-overview">Robotics MS</a>&nbsp;student, Eddie Sasagawa, joins the lab.</li><li><strong>Jan 2021</strong>:&nbsp;PI receives the&nbsp;<a href="https://cse.umn.edu/mnri/news/spring-2021-mnri-seed-grant-recipients-announced">MnRI Seed Grant</a>&nbsp;with Prof.&nbsp;<a href="https://junaedsattar.cs.umn.edu/">Sattar</a>.<br>&nbsp;</li><li><strong>Dec 2020</strong>:&nbsp;Yang Yang is selected as one of the recipients of the&nbsp;<a href="https://research.umn.edu/units/umii/funding/overview">UMII MnDRIVE Ph.D. Graduate Assistantship</a>&nbsp;(robotics area, $25K for 1 year GRA).</li><li><strong>Nov 2020</strong>: A&nbsp;<a href="https://cse.umn.edu/mnri/masters-robotics-overview">Robotics MS</a>&nbsp;student, Ross Worobel, joins the lab.</li><li><strong>Oct 2020</strong>:&nbsp;PI co-advises a CS&amp;E Ph.D. student, Song Liu, working with Prof.&nbsp;<a href="https://www-users.cs.umn.edu/~tianhe/">He</a>.</li><li><strong>Sep 2020</strong>: Two new Ph.D. students, Alireza Rezazadeh and Houjian Yu, join the lab.</li><li><strong>Aug 2020</strong>: PI co-advises an ECE Ph.D. student, Jiacheng Yuan, working with Prof.&nbsp;<a href="https://www-users.cs.umn.edu/~isler/">Isler</a>.</li><li><strong>May 2020</strong>: Our paper about&nbsp;<a href="./reachability-aware-object-grasping">reachability-aware grasping</a>&nbsp;is published in IEEE ICRA 2020.</li><li><strong>Apr 2020</strong>: Our&nbsp;<a href="https://sites.google.com/umn.edu/grasping-invisible">grasping the invisible work</a>&nbsp;is published in IEEE RA-L.<br>&nbsp;</li><li><strong>Sep 2019</strong>: A CS&amp;E MS student, Abhinav Mehta, joins the lab.</li><li><strong>Apr 2019</strong>: A CS&amp;E Ph.D. student, Yang Yang, joins the lab.<br>&nbsp;</li><li><strong>Sep 2018</strong>: Two new Ph.D. students, Xibai Lou and Hengyue Liang, join the lab.</li><li><strong>Jan 2018</strong>: PI (Prof. Choi) joins UMN ECE and establishes the Choice Robotics Lab.</li></ul></div>
      
